The '''Canadian Agency for Drugs and Technologies in Health''', or '''CADTH''', is a [[Canada|Canadian]] national organisation that provides research and analysis to healthcare decision-makers.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Rich|first=Pat|date=2018-05-07|title=Low awareness about CADTH among practising doctors in Canada|journal=Canadian Medical Association Journal |volume=190|issue=18|pages=E576|doi=10.1503/cmaj.109-5595|issn=1488-2329|pmc=5940463|pmid=29735539}}</ref>
The organisation was established in 1989 by the country's [[Government of Canada|federal government]], and those of its [[Provinces and territories of Canada|provinces and territories]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cadth.ca/about-cadth| title=About CADTH| publisher=CADTH| access-date=6 October 2017}}</ref> Before April 2006, CADTH was known as the '''Canadian Coordinating Office for Health Technology Assessment''' ('''CCOHTA''').<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cadth.ca/about-cadth/who-we-are/history| title=CADTH History| publisher=CADTH| access-date=6 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ispor.org/htaroadmaps/canadapharm.asp|title=Pharmaceutical HTA and Reimbursement Processes - Canada|website=www.ispor.org|access-date=2018-07-22}}</ref>
