{{NRIS-only|date=November 2013}} {{Infobox NRHP | name = The Planters Exchange, Inc. | image = PlantersExchange.JPG | caption = | location = 204 Second St., NW, [[Havana, Florida]] | coordinates = {{coord|30|37|28|N|84|25|2|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = Florida#USA | added = September 17, 1999 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | architect = | architecture = | area = {{convert|2.5|acre}} | governing_body = Private | refnum = 99001147<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref> }}
The '''Planter's Exchange, Inc.''' is a historic site in [[Havana, Florida|Havana]], [[Florida]]. It is located at 204 2nd Street, Northwest, and was originally a [[tobacco]] [[warehouse]]. On September 17, 1999, it was added to the [[United States|U.S.]] [[National Register of Historic Places]]. [[File:The Planters Exchange Havana, Florida 1959 view.jpg|left|thumb|The Exchange in 1959.]]
